### Next, let us provide the given income statement.

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Belle, Co.}\\
\text{Income Statement}
\end{array}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{lr}
\textbf{Description}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}\\[10pt]
\text{Sales}&\$18,900.00\\
\text{Cost of Sales}&\underline{12,800.00}\\
\text{Taxable Income}&6,100.00\\
\text{Taxes(21\%)}&\underline{1,281.00}\\
\textbf{Net Income}&\underline{\underline{\$4,819.00}}

\end{array}
$$

### Last, provide the given balance sheet.

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Belle, Inc.}\\
\text{Balance Sheet}
\end{array}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{lrlr}
\textbf{Description}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}&\textbf{Description}&\underline{\textbf{Amount}}\\[10pt]
\text{Current Assets}&\$11,700.00&\text{Liabilities}&\$15,700.00\\
\text{Fixed Assets}&\underline{26,500.00}&\text{Equity}&\underline{22,500.00}\\
\textbf{Total}&\underline{\underline{\$38,200.00}}&\textbf{Total}&\underline{\underline{\$38,200.00}}
\end{array}
$$

### Before we can calculate the retention ratio, we need to compute first the declared dividends.

The company maintains a 30% dividend payout ratio. The declared dividends are calculated by multiplying the payout ratio with the net income.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Declared Dividends}&= \text{Payout Ratio} \times \text{Net Income}\\[15pt]
&= 30\% \times \$4,819.00\\[15pt]
&= \boxed{\textbf{\$1,445.70}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the declared dividends are **$1,445.70**.

### Now that the retained earnings are available, we can compute the retention ratio.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Retention Ratio}&= \dfrac{\text{Retained Earnings}}{\text{Net Income}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\$3,373.30}{\$4,819.00}\\[15pt]
&= 0.70 \times 100\\[15pt]
&= \boxed{\textbf{70\%}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the retention ratio is **70%**.

The following assumptions were made regarding the financial plan:
&nbsp;
* Predicted increase in assets and costs are proportional to sales
&nbsp;
* Dividend payout ratio of 30\%

To determine the sustainable growth rate, let us first compute the return on equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Return on Equity}&=\frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Total Equity}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$4,819}{\$22,500}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.214}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The return on equity is 0.214.**

Now, let us compute the  dividend:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Dividend}&=\text{Net Income}\times\text{Dividend Payout Ratio}\\[12pt]
&={\$,4,819}\times{30\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$1,445.70}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The dividend is \$1,445.70.**

Now, let us compute the retained earnings:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Retained Earnings}&=\text{Net Income}-\text{Dividend}\\[12pt]
&={\$4,819}-{\$1,445.70}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$3,373.30}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The retained earnings is \$3,373.30.**

Now, let us compute the retention ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Retention Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Retained Earnings}}{\text{Net Income}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$3,373.30}{\$4,819}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.70}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{70\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The retention ratio is 70\%.**
